The paper focuses on program repair techniques for programming education, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses clustering techniques for grouping similar incorrect student attempts, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of automated techniques for generating feedback and repairs could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential use of the approach in interactive teaching settings, which could fall under the computer science education (cs.EDU) sub-category.
